  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Help Survivors of Trauma and Violence in Mosul</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Thousands of women, men and children who survived the three-year ISIS occupation live without access to medical treatment. Many survivors suffer from Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder (PTSD), anxiety, depression or chronic pain. Additionally, there is urgent need for surgical interventions and sustained medical treatment. In 2018, Jiyan Foundation established a treatment center in Mosul where doctors and psychologists treat survivors and provide transportation to our center, free of charge.</narrative>
  </description>
